The following tables give an overview of version I of the Passion, first performed in 1724. Two versions of movement numbers are given, first that of the [[Neue Bach-Ausgabe]] (NBA), then that of the older [[Bach-Werke-Verzeichnis]] (BWV). Voices appear in one of three columns, depending on the text source, Bible, contemporary poetic reflection, and chorale. The [[instrumentation]] is added, using abbreviations for instruments, followed by [[Key (music)|key]] and [[time signature]], and the NBA number of a corresponding movement within the work's symmetry.

